Structs/JSToken.html.name: JSToken
Structs/JSToken.html.abstract: A lexical token from a JS program or fragment

Protocols/JSSyntaxNode.html#/s:7JSSwift1.name: type
Protocols/JSSyntaxNode.html#/s:7JSSwift1.abstract: The type field is a string representing the AST variant type. Each subtype of Node is documented below with the specific string of its type field. You can use this field to determine which interface a node implements.

Protocols/JSSyntaxNode.html#/s:7JSSwift1.name: loc
Protocols/JSSyntaxNode.html#/s:7JSSwift1.abstract: The loc field represents the source location information of the node. If the node contains no information about the source location, the field is null; otherwise it is an object consisting of a start position (the position of the first character of the parsed source region) and an end position (the position of the first character after the parsed source region)

Protocols/JSSyntaxNode.html#/s:7JSSwift1.name: range
Protocols/JSSyntaxNode.html#/s:7JSSwift1.abstract: The optional range location for this token

Classes/JavaScriptParser/ParseOptions.ht.name: range
Classes/JavaScriptParser/ParseOptions.ht.abstract: Whether the parser should include the range.

Classes/JavaScriptParser/ParseOptions.ht.name: loc
Classes/JavaScriptParser/ParseOptions.ht.abstract: Whether the parser should include the source location

Classes/JavaScriptParser/ParseOptions.ht.name: tolerant
Classes/JavaScriptParser/ParseOptions.ht.abstract: Tolerate a few cases of syntax errors

Classes/JavaScriptParser/TokenizeOptions.name: range
Classes/JavaScriptParser/TokenizeOptions.abstract: Annotate each token with its zero-based start and end location

Classes/JavaScriptParser/TokenizeOptions.name: loc
Classes/JavaScriptParser/TokenizeOptions.abstract: Annotate each token with its column and row-based location

Classes/JavaScriptParser/TokenizeOptions.name: comment
Classes/JavaScriptParser/TokenizeOptions.abstract: Include every line and block comment in the output

Classes/JavaScriptParser.html#/s:7JSSwif.name: parseBric(script:options:)
Classes/JavaScriptParser.html#/s:7JSSwif.abstract: Parses a JavaScript script to a generic Bric tree.

Classes/JavaScriptParser.html#/s:7JSSwif.name: tokenize(javaScript:options:)
Classes/JavaScriptParser.html#/s:7JSSwif.abstract: Tokenizes the given JavaScript with options. This takes a string as an input and produces an array of tokens, a list of object representing categorized input characters.

Classes/JavaScriptParser.html.name: JavaScriptParser
Classes/JavaScriptParser.html.abstract: A tokenizer and parser for JavaScript, based on Esprima.
